This paper deals with approximation algorithms for a clustering problem, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The use of Lagrangian relaxation and the primal-dual schema suggests that this paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The focus on approximation algorithms and optimization suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of weights and the minimization of assignment costs suggests that it may belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. Finally, the use of metrics and enumeration procedures suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
